		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Normal AC adapters are unregulated and run at higher voltages unless they have the load applied to them that they were designed for.  A volt meter obviously doesn't supply much load, so you see way more than the rated value.  The power gets regulated once inside the NES/Famicom to keep a constant voltage for the parts.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


